{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review (T11 Data-migration / backfill safety [overlay]): SUBSTANTIALLY NOT-APPLICABLE, one narrow coaching item.\n\nThis plan adds a new persisted/signed field `verified_at_sha` (AC2; `## What` attested bullet), but rebar's persistence is an APPEND-ONLY event log reduced into ticket state (`append_event` → `reduce_ticket`), and the signed-verdict schemas are additive with `additionalProperties: true` (src/rebar/schemas/sign_result.schema.json:7; plan_review_verdict.schema.json:51-58 already documents `material_fingerprint` invalidation). The plan proposes NO backfill, NO blocking DDL, NO large-table rewrite, and NO rewrite of historical records — the field is forward-only on newly written events. So T11(a) expand-contract, (b) batching, (c) resumability, (d) dual-write window, and (e) rollback/data-loss all PASS as not-applicable (there is no migration to execute), except for the additive change being trivially reversible (just stop emitting the field — no data loss).\n\nONE coaching item (not a blocker):\n- [ ] State that `verified_at_sha` is an additive, forward-only field on the append-only signed-verdict record (no backfill of historical verdicts; pre-existing verdicts that lack the field remain valid/verifiable), and define re-verification semantics (a new attested run records a fresh `verified_at_sha`). Rationale: the plan never states the format-compatibility posture for records that PRE-DATE this change, so reviewers can't confirm no migration is needed. This follows the codebase's established additive-event + `material_fingerprint`-style invalidation pattern."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782519612831291001,"uuid":"ce998987-b0fa-424c-9b83-777ef91e151f"}